Design Agency Landing Page — Editorial Black & White
CATEGORY
Creative Agency / Portfolio
DESIGN STYLE
Minimalist monochrome, editorial serif typography, oversized headlines, sharp geometry, ink-black
borders
Overview
Build a striking editorial landing page for ‘Studio Void’, a high-end creative design agency. The design is
pure black and white — no colors, no gradients, no shadows. Every visual impact comes from
typographic scale, border geometry, and negative space. The hero features an oversized display
headline at 160px that bleeds off the viewport edge. Sections are separated by thick 4px horizontal
rules. Cards invert to black on hover. The aesthetic should feel like opening a luxury fashion editorial —
austere, commanding, and unforgettable.
Design Tokens
Background #FFFFFF — Pure white
Foreground #000000 — Pure ink black
Muted BG #F5F5F5 — Off-white for alt sections
Secondary text ~~ #525252 — Dark gray
Borders 1px / 2px / 4px / 8px solid #000000
Typography Playfair Display display, Source Serif 4 body, JetBrains Mono labels
Radius px — Zero everywhere, non-negotiable
Shadows. None — Depth via inversion and borders only
Page Sections
1. Navigation
— Minimal: Logo "VOID" in bold black serif left. "Work / Studio / Contact’ links right in small caps JetBrains
Mono
— Full-width 2px black border-bottom
— On scroll past 100px: thin horizontal ticker appears below nav showing ‘STUDIO VOID — CREATIVE
DESIGN — EST. MMXVIl — repeating, Framer Motion x animate

2. Hero
~ Massive H1: WE MAKE THINGS THAT MATTER" in Playfair Display Black, 10vw font-size, 0.04em
tracking, line-height 0.8
~The word MATTER" overflows and clips with overfiow-hidden on container — intentional editorial crop

— Below headline: thin horizontal line (1p) full width, then 3-column grid below it

— Col 1: ‘Scroll to explore’ in JetBrains Mono xs with animated downward arrow

— Col 2: empty — negative space is intentional

— Col 3: short paragraph, 16px Source Serif 4, about the studio

— Framer Motion: hero text enters with clipPath reveal from bottom (y-100% 0, duration 1s, staggered
words)
3. Selected Work Grid
— 4 projects ina 2x2 grid. Each cel: ful-bleed image in greyscale, project ttl in serif below, thin border
around entire cell
~ On hover: image desaturates 0 (already grey), border thickens to 4px, file inverts (white on black),
Framer Motion layout animation
~ Project metadata: client name + year in JetBrains Mono xs above image
4. Services — Horizontal Scroll
— Pinned horizontal scroll section using Framer Motion useScroll + useTransform
— Services: Branding, Web Design, Motion, Editorial, Strategy — each as a large card 60vw wide
— Card background alternates white/black. Text inverts accordingly
~ Large service number (01, 02...) in 200px light gray serif, absolutely positioned top-left of card
5. Studio Stats — Inverted Section
— Full black background section with white text
— 4 stats ina row: 200+ Projects’ / "12 Years’ /'40 Awards’ / 6 Countries’
— Each stat giant number in 96px Playfair Display, label below in mono xs
— Framer Motion countUp animation triggers on scroll into view
6. Testimonial Pull Quote
— Single testimonial fills the section: quote text at 40px italic Playfair Display
— Oversized opening quotation mark (200px) in light gray absolutely positioned
— Client name + role in JetBrains Mono below, with thin separator line
7. Contact CTA
— White section: "Let's build something remarkable * headline at 64px
~ Email input with 2px bottom border only (no box), placeholder ‘your@email com”
— "SEND button: black background, white text, uppercase, no radius
— On hover: button inverts to white background with black border and text — instant Oms transition
8. Footer
~ 3-column grid: Studio address | Nav links | ‘STUDIO VOID © 2025"
— Fullwidth 4px top border

Animations
— Hero text: clipPath reveal, staggered words, Framer Motion
_ Work gic: whielnView scale 0.95 1 + opacity, stagger 0.155
— Services: pinned horizontal scroll via useScroll transform
— Stats number countup on view entry using Framer Motion animate
— Ticker: continuous x-scroll using Framer Motion animate

